Citigroup India Subsidiaries Register 78 Percent Rise in Profit

-- B y   G e o r g e   S m i t h   A l e x a n d e r   a n d   R u t h   D a v i d
-- 
2011-06-20T14:21:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/citigroup-india-subsidiaries-register-78-percent-rise-in-profit.html
The Indian units of  Citigroup Inc. (C) ,
the third-largest U.S. lender, reported a 78 percent increase in
net income in the last financial year as loans increased.  The New York-based lender’s Indian subsidiaries posted a
net profit of 18.59 billion rupees ($413 million) in the year
ended March 31 compared with 10.4 billion rupees in the previous
year, according to an e-mailed statement today. Total assets for
the bank in  India  rose to 1.1 trillion rupees from 954.8 billion
rupees during the period.  Citigroup’s Indian unit had the largest asset base among
international banks in the South Asian nation for the year ended
March 31, data compiled by Bloomberg show. The local units of
HSBC Holdings Plc and Standard Chartered Plc had assets worth
904.25 billion rupees and 895.44 billion rupees.  By comparison,  ICICI Bank Ltd. (ICICIBC) , the South Asian nation’s
largest non-state lender with over 2,500 branches and 6,104
ATMs, reported net profit of 51.51 billion rupees for the 12
months through March 2011.  Citigroup has a network of 42 branches and 658 ATMs,
according to the statement. Profit rose as loans to corporate
clients climbed by 33 percent and to small and medium
enterprises by 35 percent, the statement showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
